The paper deals with the problem of recognizing search trees in graphs, which is a fundamental problem in graph algorithms and data structures. This problem is closely related to various subfields of computer science, such as data structures (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper presents new results for several search algorithms, including LDFS, LBFS, MCS, and MNS, which are relevant to these subfields. Therefore, it is likely that the paper belongs to one or more of these sub-categories.
